\begin{align*}
y&=2x-10\\
y&=-4x+36
\end{align*}
Setting them equal to each other, we get $2x-10=-4x+36$. Solving for $x$, we find $x=7$. Substituting this value back into one of the original equations, we get $y=4$. Thus the point of intersection is $(7,4)$. The answer is therefore $5$.</think> <answer>5</answer>

